{{about|the French expression|the African mythological tale|enfant terrible (folklore)|other uses|Les Enfants Terribles (disambiguation)}}
{{italic title}}
{{wikt|enfant terrible}}
'''''Enfant terrible''''' ({{IPAc-en|ˌ|ɒ̃|f|ɒ̃|_|t|ɛ|ˈ|r|iː|b|l|ə}}; {{IPA-fr|ɑ̃fɑ̃ tɛʁibl|lang}}; "unruly child") is a [[French language|French]] expression, traditionally referring to a child who is terrifyingly candid by saying embarrassing things to parents or others.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dictionary.reverso.net/english-cobuild/enfant%20terrible|title=enfant terrible|publisher=dictionary.reverso.net|accessdate=2017-09-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wordreference.com/definition/enfant%20terrible|title=enfant terrible|publisher=www.wordreference.com|accessdate=2017-09-28}}</ref> However, the expression has drawn multiple usage in careers of [[art]], [[fashion]], [[music]], and other [[creative arts]]. In these careers, it implies a successful "genius" who is very unorthodox, striking, and in some cases, offensive, or rebellious.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://translation.babylon.com/english/enfant%20terrible/|title=enfant terrible|publisher=translation.babylon.com|accessdate=2017-09-28}}</ref>

The ''[[Oxford English Dictionary]]'', 2nd edition, gives the definition: "A child who embarrasses his elders by untimely remarks; transf. a person who compromises his associates or his party by unorthodox or ill-considered speech or behaviour; loosely, one who acts unconventionally."

''[[Webster's Dictionary]]'' also defines an ''enfant terrible'' as an unusually successful person who is strikingly unorthodox, innovative, and/or [[avant-garde]].

==See also==
*[[Les Enfants Terribles (disambiguation)]]

