'''Mathoor Krishnamurthy''' was a [[Kannada]] writer and former Director of the [[Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan]], [[Bangalore]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Iyengar|first=Vidya|title=American art corners Bangloreans|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bangalore/report_american-art-corners-bangloreans_1440872|accessdate=6 October 2011|newspaper=DNA|date=21 Sep 2010}}</ref>  He was also instrumental in establishing the Bharatiya Vidya Bhavan in [[London]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Beyond the Seas|url=http://www.shyamalagbhave.com/beyong_sea.html|publisher=Shyamala Bhave|accessdate=6 October 2011}}</ref> He was a [[Padma Shri]] awardee.<ref>{{cite news|title=Thank you DNA, says Padma Shri Mattur|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bangalore/report_thank-you-dna-says-padma-shri-mattur_1281703|accessdate=6 October 2011|newspaper=DNA|date=12 August 2009}}</ref> He died on 6 October 2011 at the age of 82.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mathur Krishnamurthy passes away|url=http://metroslive.com/category/tv9-kannada/|publisher=TV9 Bangalore|accessdate=6 October 2011}}</ref>
