{{Forms of government}} {{About|the concept Videocracy|the 2009 documentary by [[Erik Gandini]]|Videocracy (film)}}
'''Videocracy''' is the power of the [[image]] over [[society]].<ref>''Towards a "Videocracy"? Italian Political Communication at a Turning Point'', European Journal of Communication 10 (3), 1995, pp.291-319</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20070619083400/http://www.topos.ru/veer/01/dar14.html topos.ru]</ref>
==Examples== "Voter-generated-content", such as videos on [[YouTube]], have been identified as examples of a developing videocracy.<ref>[https://archive.is/20121209175201/http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:vjb8pZ4Et1EJ:www.blogs.uni-osnabrueck.de/americanstudies/author/jakruege/+videocracy+academic&hl=pl&ct=clnk&cd=25&gl=pl&client=firefox-a American Studies at Osnabrück University website]</ref>
In [[Italy]], the election of [[Silvio Berlusconi]] as Prime Minister in 1994 was seen by many as a "media [[coup d'état]] [and] a drift towards 'videocracy'".<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=F_7QgEFjRjsC&pg=PA40&dq=videocracy&ei=aSTNSIDXGIm6zATWjeG1Cw&sig=ACfU3U2-Ag7WuvbvvsBoTiw1KdFbTRPHPQ [[Toby Miller|Miller, Toby]], ''Television: Critical Concepts in Media and Cultural Studies'', Routledge, 2003, p. 40]</ref>
John Kifner writes that in [[Romania]] a 'videocracy' was involved in the overthrow of [[Nicolae Ceauşescu]] in the "first revolution on live television".<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=s1-r6XOP2CUC&pg=PR19&dq=videocracy&lr=&ei=IS3NSOfzM5LkywS1zPWUAw&sig=ACfU3U0d_GSLHQnMAQYQlXK_jyPERUak1g Annabelle Sreberny-Mohammadi, Ali Mohammadi, ''Small Media, Big Revolution: Communication, Culture, and the Iranian Revolution'', University of Minnesota Press, 1994, p. xix]</ref>
==See also== [[Logocracy]] - a system where the words are the key to power, seen by some as an important adjunct to videocracy, by others as its [[antithesis]].<ref>[http://www.vavilon.ru/texts/prim/genis4-5.html vavilon.ru] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150528024554/http://www.vavilon.ru/texts/prim/genis4-5.html |date=2015-05-28 }}</ref> * [[Information Age]] * [[Internet]] * [[Netocracy]] * [[Propaganda]]
